-- Real estate group Deutsche Annington launches public offer for Gagfah 
-- By Arno Schuetze
-- Fri Dec 19, 2014 03:28AM EST
-- None



FRANKFURT, Dec 19 (Reuters) - Germany's biggest real estate firm Deutsche Annington <ANNGn.DE> on Friday launched its public offer for third-ranked rival Gagfah <GFJG.DE> in a 3.9 billion euro ($4.8 bln) cash and shares deal.

Gagfah shareholders can tender their shares until January 2015, Deutsche Annington said in a statement, adding the minimum acceptance level lies at 57 percent of all outstanding Gagfah shares.